==Spanish==
===Etymology===
From Old Catalan [[faena#Old Catalan|faena]] ‘task, chore’, from Latin [[facienda]] ‘things to do’, from [[facere]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /fa'ena/

===Noun===
'''faena''' ''f''
# a [[task]] or [[job]]; a [[duty]]
# ''(Latin America)'' compulsory labour or work
# a dirty trick
# ''(bullfighting)'' a series of passes performed by a [[matador]] with cape or sword before the kill

